    "description": "Data_Break is a darkly humorous RPG, inspired by games like Earthbound, Undertale and LISA: The Painful. You play as an office drone who lives a seemingly ordinary life, but something isn't right... A mysterious stranger will soon set into motion a series of events that gradually reveal the horrifying truth...<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" >The full game features</h2><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Experience a mundane existence in game, as well as in real life! <br></li><li>Get showered, go to work, eat, sleep!<br></li><li>A PLAYABLE TOILET!<br></li><li>Beat or befriend foes like spiders, the elderly, teens, someone that definitely isn't Mickey Mouse, your boss, and more.<br></li><li>Lots of choices, and some that will bite you in the *** later!<br></li><li>Care for your cat. Or not because you are heartless POS.<br></li><li>An awesome original and authentic 8-bit soundtrack<br></li><li>Lots of jokes, references and Easter eggs<br></li><li>Multiple endings<br></li><li>Learn the meaning of life*</li></ul>*you might not learn the meaning of life.",
